To add a rule description, you can use IpRanges block.

&gt; **IpRanges** - A set of IP permissions to specify multiple rules and a description for the rule.

```
&#39;IpRanges&#39;: [
  {
     &#39;CidrIp&#39;: &#39;0.0.0.0/0&#39;,
     &#39;Description&#39;: &#39;SSH Access&#39;
  }
]
```

Check the [documentation](https://boto3.amazonaws.com/v1/documentation/api/latest/reference/services/ec2.html#EC2.SecurityGroup.authorize_ingress) for the detailed example. There isn&#39;t a `Description` key on the top level but you can find it from the value of `IpPermissions` and `IpRanges`.

```
response = security_group.authorize_ingress(
    CidrIp=&#39;string&#39;,
    FromPort=123,
    GroupName=&#39;string&#39;,
    IpPermissions=[
        {
            &#39;FromPort&#39;: 123,
            &#39;IpProtocol&#39;: &#39;string&#39;,
            &#39;IpRanges&#39;: [
                {
                    &#39;CidrIp&#39;: &#39;string&#39;,
                    &#39;Description&#39;: &#39;string&#39;
