You can use CSS media queries to detect the width of the screen which is a better method to detect if the device is mobile rather than user agent parsing.

For example

```
@media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
  body {
    background-image: url(...);
  }
}
```

Or if you want to detect it form JS see:
https://www.w3schools.com/howto/howto_js_media_queries.asp

if there is a background that you need to set it for body and a div in different screen size you can do it just with CSS.

add a class to the div that you want to set the background for it in mobile, use CSS media code as bellow to add the background to that div and the body

    @media screen and (max-width: 768px) {
     .examplediv {
      Background-image:url(&#39;&#39;);
     }
    }
    
    @media screen and (min-width: 768px) {
     body{
      Background-image:url(&#39;&#39;);
     }
    }

